column2: This is a seat map file for YFC's ticket system.
Class 1 seats reserved 4 rows by 16 & 16, class 2 seats reserved 8 rows by 20 & 20, no general seats
Centered aisle two spaces wide & horizontal aisle between class 1 and 2
The first column should contain a command name as follows.
“Row” entries should contain a row of seats with a class number in each location, or blank for empty spots like aisles.
Or, row entries can optionally be entered with seat codes in the form C-R-L, where C=class, R=row, and L=column.
“General” entries are followed by a number of general admission seats, and then a class number in the next cell.
“Theatre” entries specify a theatre id number if you are adding seats to an existing theatre (optional).
“Zone” entries specify a name for the zone you are entering (optional, the default is “Main”).
“Note” entries are for documentation, and will be ignored.
Save this file as a Comma Separated Values or CSV file.
Blank rows will also be ignored.
